# Completion Review

- Active implementation slices are archived: production pipeline composition,
  metadata persistence, apply-precondition derivation, and scheduler service
  entrypoint.
- Production CLI dispatch now composes repository-backed pipeline stages and
  diagnostics from validated startup config.
- Metadata sync output is persisted through the repository; dry-run validates
  without writes.
- Apply fails closed from repository guard state and exits 5 when DB/snapshot,
  desired state, quota safety, or probe/smoke evidence is missing or failing.
- `serve` owns the scheduler cron path and routes scheduled/manual/event/urgent
  triggers through persistent run locks.
- Scanner and free-registry persistence now write provider/account/catalog,
  endpoint, registry snapshot, and free-model rows through repository methods;
  source regression tests reject embedded table SQL in those stage modules.
- Production composition now dispatches `sync-free-registry` and
  `scan-providers` through registry/scanner adapters, removes the shared
  `_domain_stage_adapter` no-op, and requires explicit per-stage adapters for
  canonical domain stages at the adapter-backed boundary.
- Unwired canonical stages now fail closed with `not_implemented` (exit 3), and
  the executable effect harness rejects `success` results that lack a declared
  repository write, OmniRoute call, or idempotent no-change effect.
- Remaining unwired stages are tracked by active OpenSpec slices:
  none.
- Production composition now wires `model-matching`, `quota-research`, and
  `access-classification` to their domain modules. Matching writes canonical
  endpoint bindings, quota research writes content-hashed summary snapshots and
  capped rules, and access classification writes canonical attribution status
  plus evidence. Missing quota payloads fail closed.
- Production composition now wires `probing`, `telemetry-sync`, and
  `quota-sync`. Probing is gated on confirmed access with remaining capacity and
  persists probe rows, telemetry sync writes normalized health observations, and
  quota sync writes live quota observations plus remaining-quota state.
- Production composition now wires `role-scoring`, `allocation`, and `diff`.
  Scoring persists per-role endpoint scores, allocation persists one planned
  combo target set per role with constraint reports, and diff persists minimal
  combo changes without mutating OmniRoute.
- Production composition now wires `apply` and `audit` end to end. Apply checks
  repository-backed preconditions, mutates only `fmo-` combos, runs the real
  smoke path without `/api/combos/test`, rolls back on smoke failure, and
  reports the real combo-test signal. Audit persists apply records and drift
  detection.
- Run-lock acquisition is now database-atomic through a partial unique index on
  active held lock rows; repository tests cover two independent connections,
  fresh schema installs, and migration installs.
- Code Simplifier review cleaned the new scheduler tests by sharing the partial
  index assertion and making concurrent-thread completion explicit.
- Remaining deferred repo-level work: none discovered in this slice.
